A Southport man has been charged over a sickening crime where a cat's blood was smeared on a garage door of a Gold Coast home and a car set alight during an early morning attack.

The 19-year-old man will appear in Southport Magistrates Court on Wednesday charged with injuring animals by night, wilful damage and arson.

It is alleged he killed a cat during the incident as well as setting a car on fire and damaging the garage door of the home.

The owner of the cat that was slaughtered in the June 17 attack, Mady White, told Daily Mail Australia she had no idea how Moo - a black and white feline - became entangled in the Arundel crime.

