Ms White said she had not noticed her cat was missing from her Bundall home - about 10km away from the Hazel Court address where the crime took place - until Gold Coast police officers showed up at her door.

'I knew of the threatening stuff from the news but I didn’t know it was my cat until the police came,' the 20-year-old said.

'It didn’t feel real. I thought I had seen her that day, but I had been unwell that day and the day before so I was unsure when I had last seen her.

'I was asleep when I suspected she was taken by one of my friends, which would have been Monday night.'

